with me too!

145
00:12:10.730 --> 00:12:11.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Uh, hello?

146
00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:15.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Maverick] <i>How unfortunate that it</i>
<i>has to come to this.</i>

147
00:12:16.861 --> 00:12:17.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Barnaby] Maverick!

148
00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:21.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why do you have her comm unit?</i>

149
00:12:21.115 --> 00:12:22.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah, Wild Tiger.

150
00:12:23.117 --> 00:12:25.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If only you had allowed
yourself to be captured,

151
00:12:26.037 --> 00:12:28.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
none of your friends would
have had to get involved.

152
00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What the hell have
you done with them?

153
00:12:30.917 --> 00:12:32.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have no need for concern.

154
00:12:33.127 --> 00:12:34.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everyone's safe for now.

155
00:12:35.004 --> 00:12:36.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All the heroes,

156
00:12:36.256 --> 00:12:37.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and your daughter.</i>

157
00:12:38.174 --> 00:12:39.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you just say?

158
00:12:40.593 --> 00:12:42.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think I'm gonna let
you threaten my daughter?

159
00:12:43.221 --> 00:12:45.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You monster, she's
just a little girl!

160
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:49.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The two of you have turned into
a massive liability for me.

161
00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:52.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just can't have you boys
causing any more problems.

162
00:12:52.397 --> 00:12:55.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you can save them all by
simply surrendering to me.

163
00:12:56.359 --> 00:12:59.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I will be waiting for
you at Justice Tower.

164
00:12:59.988 --> 00:13:00.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts angrily]

165
00:13:01.823 --> 00:13:02.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dammit!

166
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:07.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He won't get away with it.
I won't allow it!

167
00:13:08.621 --> 00:13:12.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Kotetsu] Justice Tower...
justice my ass!

168
00:13:22.552 --> 00:13:23.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where am I?

169
00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:26.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What the...
What's going on?

170
00:13:26.139 --> 00:13:28.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am gonna bitch slap
someone for this!

171
00:13:28.516 --> 00:13:31.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hello? Hey!
Can anybody hear me out there?

172
00:13:41.571 --> 00:13:43.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rise and shine, Miss Rose.

173
00:13:44.449 --> 00:13:45.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasp]

174
00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:52.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[male mechanical voice]
<i>You have been expected.</i>

175
00:13:53.374 --> 00:13:54.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please, come inside.</i>

176
00:13:57.420 --> 00:13:58.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hold on.

177
00:13:58.921 --> 00:14:01.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We should be careful.
It might be a trap.

178
00:14:01.924 --> 00:14:05.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't care if it is.
Come on, there's no time to lose!

179
00:14:08.222 --> 00:14:11.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female announcer] <i>Welcome. And thank you</i>
<i>for choosing to visit Justice Tower.</i>

180
00:14:12.018 --> 00:14:13.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We're happy to have</i>
<i>you as our guest.</i>

181
00:14:14.103 --> 00:14:17.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>This elevator will take you to</i>
<i>the rooftop observation deck</i>

182
00:14:17.607 --> 00:14:20.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>in the most exclusive section</i>
<i>of the tower, the Gold Stage.</i>

183
00:14:21.694 --> 00:14:23.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Now arriving at</i>
<i>observation deck.</i>

184
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:30.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why would he bring us
all the way up here?

185
00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:36.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Saito]
Perfection!

186
00:14:37.168 --> 00:14:39.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never expected
my invention to be used like this!

187
00:14:40.254 --> 00:14:43.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's great, but I thought
their hero suits already had cameras.

188
00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:45.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why bother using
that bug thing?

189
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:47.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's simple.

190
00:14:47.136 --> 00:14:50.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Communications between heroes are
relayed using a special private network

191
00:14:50.723 --> 00:14:53.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that's encrypted to prevent data
from being diverted to the wrong hands.

192
00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:56.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However, I've been unable
to access the network,

193
00:14:56.562 --> 00:14:58.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which indicates that Maverick
has seized control of it.

194
00:14:59.023 --> 00:15:01.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you getting all this?
-Not really, no.

195
00:15:01.442 --> 00:15:04.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[microphone feedback]
Well then, I'll clarify!

196
00:15:04.362 --> 00:15:06.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's simple: communications
between heroes are--

197
00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:10.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let me guess; We can't use the
cameras on their suits, right?

198
00:15:10.451 --> 00:15:11.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How succinctly put.

199
00:15:11.953 --> 00:15:14.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if we can learn
what's going on inside,

200
00:15:14.497 --> 00:15:17.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm hopeful that we may be able
to help rescue the other captive heroes.

201
00:15:24.507 --> 00:15:26.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kaede! Where are you Kaede?

202
00:15:26.384 --> 00:15:28.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kotetsu! Calm down!

203
00:15:28.302 --> 00:15:30.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How can I calm down
when he's got my girl?

204
00:15:30.888 --> 00:15:32.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's my fault she's in danger.

205
00:15:40.314 --> 00:15:42.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey jackass, where the
hell is my daughter?

206
00:15:42.191 --> 00:15:45.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Easy now. We don't know
what kind of NEXT we're dealing with.

207
00:15:45.862 --> 00:15:47.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't just stand
there looking stupid.

208
00:15:48.239 --> 00:15:49.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Answer me!

209
00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:50.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasp]

210
00:15:51.742 --> 00:15:54.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look at that!
What the hell is that thing?!

211
00:15:58.249 --> 00:15:59.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's no NEXT...

212
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:00.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's a robot.

213
00:16:01.836 --> 00:16:03.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Weren't expecting that, eh?</i>

214
00:16:04.422 --> 00:16:06.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It has been far too long, Barnaby.</i>

215
00:16:07.008 --> 00:16:08.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barnaby]
Rotwang...

216
00:16:08.301 --> 00:16:09.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

217
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:13.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose it must be quite a shock
to run into me again, huh?

218
00:16:13.973 --> 00:16:15.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shut up!

219
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:20.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maverick, Where's Kaede?
I want to speak with her. Put her on!

220
00:16:20.605 --> 00:16:24.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now now. You should be far more
concerned with your own fate.

221
00:16:24.775 --> 00:16:26.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>What are you</i>
<i>talking about?</i>

222
00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:28.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you really think I'm going to
let you leave here alive?

223
00:16:29.113 --> 00:16:31.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh please. I'll crush this
tin can in a second!

224
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:36.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will you? I don't know, you had quite
a difficult time battling sis.

225
00:16:37.038 --> 00:16:40.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And H-01 is even more</i>
<i>technologically advanced.</i>

226
00:16:41.125 --> 00:16:43.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>His power levels are</i>
<i>far beyond hers.</i>

227
00:16:48.424 --> 00:16:50.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your little hero pals
tried their best,

228
00:16:50.676 --> 00:16:54.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but even with their combined strength they
couldn't so much as put a dent in him.

229
00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:55.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

230
00:16:57.183 --> 00:16:58.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How will you fare?

231
00:16:58.768 --> 00:17:00.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now's your chance to
turn tail and run!

232
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:03.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Screw you. And screw him!

233
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that idiot!

234
00:17:07.151 --> 00:17:08.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Astounding.

235
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:09.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

236
00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:12.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A fully operational battle
android? Impossible!

237
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:15.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Maverick] <i>I was quite impressed by the</i>
<i>technology he employed</i>

238
00:17:15.535 --> 00:17:17.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>during the last android incident.</i>

239
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:19.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>So I made a deal</i>
<i>with Dr. Rotwang.</i>

240
00:17:20.081 --> 00:17:23.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I gave him this facility and</i>
<i>every resource he desired...</i>

241
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:27.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Now you see the fruits</i>
<i>of my labor: H-01!</i>

242
00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:32.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I've finally created the ultimate being,</i>
<i>one that towers above the human race!</i>

243
00:17:32.218 --> 00:17:35.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maverick, what the hell are you
hoping to accomplish here?!

244
00:17:37.014 --> 00:17:38.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've come to realize something.

245
00:17:39.183 --> 00:17:42.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Androids are the ideal embodiment
of justice in this world.

246
00:17:43.437 --> 00:17:46.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have no need for you flawed
NEXT anymore.

247
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:49.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>H-01 will replace every</i>
<i>hero in this city.</i>

248
00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:52.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A glorious new age will begin!</i>

249
00:17:52.822 --> 00:17:55.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How dare you call this
hunk of junk a hero?

250
00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:58.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must understand
how wondrous this is, Barnaby!

251
00:17:58.703 --> 00:18:02.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The day has come when robotics
will play a crucial role in society!

252
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your parents' dream has
finally come true--!

253
00:18:04.542 --> 00:18:05.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This wasn't their dream!

254
00:18:06.836 --> 00:18:08.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rotwang] <i>You may fight him</i>
<i>together if you wish.</i>

255
00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:12.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The data from this encounter</i>
<i>will be used for future development.</i>

256
00:18:13.134 --> 00:18:16.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Unless you defeat H-01,</i>
<i>you can't save anyone.</i>

257
00:18:16.804 --> 00:18:20.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Not this fair city.</i>
<i>Not one of your precious friends.</i>

258
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:21.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Not even your daughter.</i>

259
00:18:22.268 --> 00:18:23.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasp]

260
00:18:23.686 --> 00:18:25.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Such a poor,
innocent girl.

261
00:18:25.813 --> 00:18:29.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of this would've happened
if she didn't have you for a father.

262
00:18:29.984 --> 00:18:33.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kaede, I swear I'll
get you out of this.

263
00:18:37.366 --> 00:18:41.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
After that day, the villagers knew they
could count on the giant of the mountain

264
00:18:41.287 --> 00:18:43.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to protect them forever and ever. The end.

265
00:18:43.539 --> 00:18:44.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Read it again,
Daddy!

266
00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:46.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laugh] That was the third time!

267
00:18:46.876 --> 00:18:48.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's the matter, Mom?

268
00:18:48.127 --> 00:18:51.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All you need to know is that you
can count on your dad and me

269
00:18:51.213 --> 00:18:53.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to protect you forever and ever.

270
00:18:55.593 --> 00:18:58.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I won't let you get away
with this any longer!

271
00:19:01.390 --> 00:19:03.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Rise and shine, Miss Rose.</i>

272
00:19:05.144 --> 00:19:06.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who am I speaking to?

273
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:10.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Where are the others?
What did you do with Kaede?

274
00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:14.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Never fear, the girl is safe.</i>
<i>Your friends on the other hand...</i>

275
00:19:16.739 --> 00:19:19.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh thank goodness! I hope
everyone is all right!

276
00:19:19.367 --> 00:19:21.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can someone explain
what is going on?!

277
00:19:21.410 --> 00:19:24.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I remember being defeated
by the fake Tiger...

278
00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:27.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You bastard! Let us out
of here or I'll end you!

279
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:28.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Silence, you freaks!

280
00:19:29.377 --> 00:19:32.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've locked you sub-human pieces
of garbage away in these cages

281
00:19:33.005 --> 00:19:34.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because that is where
animals belong.

282
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:36.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rock Bison]
<i>What'd you call us?</i>

283
00:19:36.258 --> 00:19:37.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's some kind of NEXT hater.

284
00:19:38.135 --> 00:19:41.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've embraced the obvious, that
your era has come to an end!

285
00:19:41.847 --> 00:19:46.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now surrender your title as protectors
of the city to H-01, the new hero!

286
00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:47.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

287
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:50.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Blue Rose] <i>H-01? You mean</i>
<i>the phony Tiger?</i>

288
00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:52.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rock Bison]
<i>You gotta be out of your mind!</i>

289
00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:55.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That lousy pile of bolts could</i>
<i>never replace us!</i>

290
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's a pretty ironic statement,

291
00:19:57.863 --> 00:20:00.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
considering he easily defeated
every one of you!

292
00:20:00.700 --> 00:20:04.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No matter how strong that thing is,
androids are just mindless weapons

293
00:20:04.495 --> 00:20:06.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that rely on humans to control them!

294
00:20:06.789 --> 00:20:08.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say that as if it's a bad thing.

295
00:20:09.458 --> 00:20:13.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen, you crazy bitch,
You shouldn't underestimate us heroes.

296
00:20:14.004 --> 00:20:17.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When we hear the cries of the
people, we feel their pain.

297
00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:20.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We even help criminals repent
and rehabilitate themselves.

298
00:20:20.970 --> 00:20:23.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No cold piece of
machinery can do that!

299
00:20:23.597 --> 00:20:24.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, he's right!

300
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:28.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're real heroes because
at our core we're humans with hearts!

301
00:20:28.936 --> 00:20:31.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I could never have
become a hero by myself.

302
00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:35.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was only able to come this far because
of the bond I have with my friends!

303
00:20:35.609 --> 00:20:38.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Heh. Oh, you're</i>
<i>making me all teary.</i>

304
00:20:38.904 --> 00:20:40.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If that's true,</i>
<i>then prove it!</i>

305
00:20:41.365 --> 00:20:44.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If this "human heart" of yours is
really so special,

306
00:20:44.285 --> 00:20:45.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
then why don't you show me?

307
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:48.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A little demonstration
of your empathy.

308
00:20:49.165 --> 00:20:50.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

309
00:20:51.125 --> 00:20:53.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately you and your
pals are all going to die.

310
00:20:54.128 --> 00:20:57.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You see, those collars around
your necks are actually bombs

311
00:20:57.423 --> 00:20:58.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
set to explode any moment now.

312
00:21:01.010 --> 00:21:05.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I will spare one of your lives
if you pass a small test of your humanity.

313
00:21:05.473 --> 00:21:07.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Only the fastest
will make it.

314
00:21:07.433 --> 00:21:09.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you want to be saved,
all you have to do is reach up

315
00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:12.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and flip the deactivation switch
on your collar.

316
00:21:12.605 --> 00:21:14.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
However there is one catch...

317
00:21:15.191 --> 00:21:18.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The moment you flip your switch
everyone else will blow up!

318
00:21:22.448 --> 00:21:23.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Doesn't it sound fun?</i>

319
00:21:24.408 --> 00:21:27.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You have until Tiger and</i>
<i>Barnaby are defeated by H-01.</i>

320
00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:31.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The second they lose, all of you</i>
<i>costumed idiots will go "boom,"</i>

321
00:21:31.665 --> 00:21:33.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>if none of you has hit their switch.</i>

322
00:21:33.959 --> 00:21:36.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And don't get any bright ideas!</i>

323
00:21:36.879 --> 00:21:41.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I catch any of you trying to use your
creepy powers to wriggle out of this,

324
00:21:41.175 --> 00:21:43.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll just blow you
up on the spot!

325
00:21:44.845 --> 00:21:49.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>So what do you think? Do you still</i>
<i>have faith in your precious friendship?</i>

326
00:21:49.475 --> 00:21:53.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Wouldn't it be much wiser to</i>
<i>betray your so-called friends</i>

327
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:56.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>before one of them</i>
<i>betrays you, "heroes?"</i>

328
00:21:56.607 --> 00:21:59.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Well, the game is set and</i>
<i>the players are ready.</i>

329
00:21:59.276 --> 00:22:01.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The moment that Tiger and</i>
<i>Barnaby's fight begins,</i>

330
00:22:02.071 --> 00:22:03.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>your fight</i>
<i>begins as well.</i>

331
00:22:04.240 --> 00:22:08.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[mad cackling]

332
00:22:08.494 --> 00:22:10.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hold on!
Wait, dammit!

333
00:22:11.372 --> 00:22:12.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is anyone there?

334
00:22:21.423 --> 00:22:22.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's do this.

335
00:22:24.385 --> 00:22:25.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm with you.

